- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a meta-heuristic algorithm inspired by foraging behaviors of beetles, which falls under the scope of evolutionary computing. 
- cs.OH (Other Computer Science) is also likely as the paper introduces a new variant of the existing algorithm and proposes a new approach for constraint handling, which can be considered as a novel contribution to the field. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with optimization problems, which is a common topic in AI research. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses normalization to simplify the algorithm, which can be considered as a form of data preprocessing commonly used in machine learning. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but still possible as the paper deals with optimization problems with constraints, which can be considered as a control problem in some contexts.
